2022 - the year I fell back in love with running. 🏃🏼‍♀️

I started running in college as a means to lose weight. On average I ran at least 4 miles a day, and simply did it because I enjoyed it. I picked it back up in 2019, and thanks to @mrskyoung I picked it up even more consistently in 2022. In 2023 I strive to run even more races, at least 1000 miles, and make memories to last a lifetime. (and hope my knee survives). Here’s to hundreds and thousands of more miles in 2023!

Happiest stay on earth! ✨

We started our Disneyland trip off with two nights at the Disneyland Hotel and we absolutely loved it! Our room had a great view of the pool area and the parks, the pool area was top notch, the food and drinks at Tangaroa Terrace and Trader Sam’s were DELISH, the CMs were so incredible, and it was just all around a great experience. 

Our only qualms were: the Wi-Fi in our building didn’t work and the cell service was weak. Usually this wouldn’t be a huge issue, but Abner had grad school homework to work on, so that was a pain for him. There is a lot of construction going on for the new DVC tower, which is noisy and caused some detours on the surrounding walkways. While it is right across the street from Downtown Disney, it is still quite a trek to the parks. We have found staying at a neighboring hotel is a lot faster to get to the parks. 

All that being said, we would like to stay here again, or even check out the Grand Californian or Pixar Place once it’s construction is done. There’s just something special about a Disney hotel. ✨

The most magical race on earth ✨ 

I am still on cloud 9 from Sunday’s marathon. In 2023 I set out to take my training for Dopey to Dumbo for a whole new level. I ended up running over 1100 miles, running long runs every weekend with @kendall.hein_ @disneywithshruthi @beccalfischer and @annikaspaintbrush when I could. Incorporated speed work, (who is she?!) built base milage and volume, and just overall became a much stronger runner! It was such a rewarding feeling seeing all of my hard work come to fruition during Sunday’s race, and see how easy it felt for me. The fact that I was able to ride Everest, meet a character, see friends on Main Street, and have a bathroom break and still run a sub 4:30?! I still don’t believe that I did it. 

That all being said, this weekend has made me realize my potential may be greater than I ever dreamed of, and my running journey is so far from over. 🤩 Coast to Coast, here I come! 🏃🏼‍♀️

#rundisney #runner #runnergirl #wdwmarathon #disneycastlife #rundopey #dopeychallenge #rundisney2024

Just call me Michael Phelps. 🏅

71 miles. 7 races. A marathon PR. 3 challenges. 2 coasts. And one very tired, but proud Rebekah. 

This Coast to Coast and Dopey to Dumbo experience has been incredibly memorable. I poured so many hours of training to make sure my body was ready for this, and as fun as it was, I will never run back to back race weekends again. 😂 I’m so glad I got to be apart of the first race weekend back at Disneyland, and I got to do it with so many incredible runners and friends. 🫶🏼

I also want to say a huge thank you to my number one supporter during all of this: @abnertorresmartinez ❤️

Now, it’s time to rest! (Until princess weekend in 5 weeks. 🫠)
